# UI Components Guidelines

General:
- Use shadcn/ui primitives from `components/ui` and shared patterns from `components/app-ui`
- Keep components controlled/stateless when possible; lift state to pages
- Ensure accessibility: ARIA labels, keyboard navigation, focus management

MultiSelect (`components/app-ui/multi-select.tsx`):
- Use `Command` for search; set `CommandItem.value` to display text (`option.name`) so search works
- Do not nest `<button>` inside shadcn `Button` (avoid hydration errors). Use a `div` with `role="button"`, `tabIndex=0`, and `onKeyDown` for Enter/Space
- Props: `options`, `selected`, `onChange`, `placeholder`, `searchPlaceholder`, `emptyText`, `maxHeight`, `disabled`
- Selected items are shown as `Badge` chips with removable affordance

Confirmation:
- Use `ConfirmationModal` for destructive actions; wire `onConfirm`/`onCancel`

Pagination:
- Use `PaginationControls` with `currentPage` and `totalPages` from `response.meta`

Skeletons:
- Use `Skeleton` for loading states; ensure layout stability

